WEBVTT

00:01.634 --> 00:04.371
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

00:04.437 --> 00:12.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:12.445 --> 00:14.681
<i>- ♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:14.748 --> 00:16.416
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:16.483 --> 00:18.752
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:18.818 --> 00:24.424
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:24.491 --> 00:26.326
<i>♪ Harvey ♪</i>

00:26.393 --> 00:29.596
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:31.664 --> 00:33.166
<i>- Mi-mi-mi-mi-mi-mi-mi!</i>

00:33.233 --> 00:35.902
Mi-mo-mo-moo-moo-moo-ma!

00:35.969 --> 00:37.003
{\an3}Little sis,

00:37.070 --> 00:39.072
{\an3}I asked you here
for a reason.

00:39.139 --> 00:40.874
This is a little embarrassing,

00:40.940 --> 00:44.644
but, I just got so excited
thinking about meeting you,

00:44.711 --> 00:46.045
I wrote you a song.

00:46.112 --> 00:48.515
So feel free to clap along.

00:48.581 --> 00:49.816
[clears throat]

00:49.883 --> 00:53.019
♪ Little sister of mine ♪

00:53.086 --> 00:55.855
♪ I hope you hatch really soon ♪

00:55.922 --> 01:00.126
♪ 'Cause once you're here,
we'll have so much fun ♪

01:00.193 --> 01:03.663
♪ Playing all day in the sun ♪

01:03.730 --> 01:07.133
♪ Little sister of mine ♪

01:07.200 --> 01:10.069
♪ I'm your big brother, Harvey ♪

01:10.136 --> 01:13.473
♪ And I'll always
be there for you ♪

01:13.540 --> 01:17.777
{\an1}♪ 'Cause that's what
big brothers do ♪

01:17.844 --> 01:25.985
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:27.987 --> 01:28.955
- Knock, knock.

01:29.022 --> 01:30.356
{\an1}- Freeze!
This is the police.

01:30.423 --> 01:33.026
And you're under arrest
for having too much fun!

01:33.092 --> 01:35.762
{\an3}- Ha!
Guilty as charged, officer.

01:35.829 --> 01:36.830
What's up, guys?

01:36.896 --> 01:38.064
{\an8}- We just wanted
to grab that box

01:38.131 --> 01:39.566
{\an8}full of your old baby things.

01:39.632 --> 01:41.401
{\an7}It's not like
you're using these anymore.

01:41.468 --> 01:43.970
{\an3}- And we have to get ready
for the bugaboo.

01:44.037 --> 01:46.239
- The bugaboo?
You mean me?

01:46.306 --> 01:48.141
- No, the baby, silly.

01:48.208 --> 01:51.144
- Oh, but I thought
I was the bugaboo.

01:51.211 --> 01:54.247
{\an1}- Oh, honey, you'll always
be the first bugaboo.

01:54.314 --> 01:56.816
{\an1}The baby's going
to be the new bugaboo.

01:56.883 --> 01:59.252
- The new bugaboo?

01:59.319 --> 02:01.354
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

02:01.421 --> 02:02.722
{\an3}- So yeah,
there's no way

02:02.789 --> 02:04.791
{\an3}that Piri has
that much bounce in her hair

02:04.858 --> 02:06.025
and didn't get a perm.

02:06.092 --> 02:07.827
{\an3}But anyways,
how are you buddy?

02:07.894 --> 02:11.364
How's your heart?

02:11.431 --> 02:13.233
{\an3}Get off! Get off!
Get off! Get off! Get off!

02:13.299 --> 02:14.934
[bunnies laughing
and scurrying]

02:15.001 --> 02:16.536
- I've just been wondering:

02:16.603 --> 02:19.239
{\an1}how do things change
when you have siblings?

02:19.305 --> 02:22.909
{\an3}- Oh, Harvey,
you sweet, innocent marigold.

02:22.976 --> 02:25.345
Everything changes.

02:25.411 --> 02:27.313
- But it's a good change?

02:27.380 --> 02:30.083
- It's bad.
Very bad.

02:30.149 --> 02:31.351
It's crazy, buddy.

02:31.417 --> 02:32.752
There's so many of us

02:32.819 --> 02:34.654
{\an3}that sometimes
my parents forget my name.

02:34.721 --> 02:36.956
{\an1}- But your name
is so charming and memorable.

02:37.023 --> 02:38.525
{\an3}- Thank you!
I know.

02:38.591 --> 02:42.328
Harvey, imagine this carrot
is your parents' love.

02:44.297 --> 02:46.399
{\an1}- Aah!
Your siblings took it all!

02:46.466 --> 02:47.901
- You want the carrot, Harvey?

02:47.967 --> 02:49.435
{\an1}- Yes!

02:49.502 --> 02:51.771
{\an3}- Well, you can't have it.
It's gone.

02:51.838 --> 02:54.207
- But I need it!

02:54.274 --> 02:56.643
{\an3}- No!
Don't you get it?

02:56.709 --> 02:58.778
{\an3}I used to have
the whole carrot,

02:58.845 --> 03:01.881
{\an3}and they took it,
'cause that's what siblings do.

03:01.948 --> 03:03.283
- This is worse than I thought.

03:03.349 --> 03:04.984
I got to do something.

03:05.051 --> 03:06.386
{\an3}- You know,
it's not so bad

03:06.452 --> 03:09.055
{\an3}when I've got
a friend like you, Harvey.

03:09.122 --> 03:10.256
{\an3}Oh.

03:11.791 --> 03:13.259
- [panting]

03:13.326 --> 03:15.728
I don't want things to change!

03:15.795 --> 03:18.865
I got to to do something.

03:18.932 --> 03:20.533
Oh, hey, sis.

03:20.600 --> 03:23.403
{\an1}It sure is crowded in here,
wouldn't you say?

03:23.469 --> 03:26.039
Heh-heh-heh.

03:26.105 --> 03:28.074
{\an3}Yeah, maybe one of us
should move out.

03:28.141 --> 03:32.145
You'd be okay
with leaving, right?

03:32.211 --> 03:33.546
Don't worry, sis,

03:33.613 --> 03:35.715
{\an1}I'm gonna find
a great new home for you.

03:35.782 --> 03:37.016
<i>[anxious music]</i>

03:37.083 --> 03:38.418
No.

03:38.484 --> 03:40.720
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:40.787 --> 03:41.654
{\an3}No.

03:41.721 --> 03:43.957
- Oh yes, this is quite lovely.

03:44.023 --> 03:45.959
I love picnics.

03:46.025 --> 03:47.493
{\an1}I can't wait
to eat my sandwich.

03:47.560 --> 03:48.728
Oh.

03:48.795 --> 03:50.129
Meh.

03:51.898 --> 03:54.934
I wonder if Jeremy
would be a good dad.

03:55.001 --> 03:55.969
Hmmm.

03:56.035 --> 03:57.737
<i>[fantastical music]</i>

03:57.804 --> 04:00.173
- Daughter.
- Yes, perfect dad?

04:00.239 --> 04:02.008
I made you silly-face pancakes

04:02.075 --> 04:03.910
because I absolutely adore you.

04:03.977 --> 04:05.378
- Whillikers!

04:05.445 --> 04:08.047
- Life was a wasteland
before I met you.

04:08.114 --> 04:09.916
- Truly, I could not have asked

04:09.983 --> 04:12.619
for a better upbringing!

04:12.685 --> 04:13.853
- Yeah!

04:15.421 --> 04:17.423
This is for the best, egg.

04:20.360 --> 04:22.428
- Huh? Is someone there? Oh!

04:22.495 --> 04:24.130
Whoa!

04:24.197 --> 04:26.499
Did I just lay an egg?

04:26.566 --> 04:27.634
Wha--wha--wha?

04:27.700 --> 04:28.568
This is so exciting!

04:28.635 --> 04:30.937
Aah! Aah! Aah!
Aah! Aah! Aah!

04:31.004 --> 04:33.740
- Whoo! I'm still the bugaboo.

04:33.806 --> 04:34.774
This is good.

04:34.841 --> 04:36.342
<i>[playful music]</i>

04:36.409 --> 04:38.478
<i>- Listen, I know</i>
<i>a natural curl when I see one,</i>

04:38.544 --> 04:40.747
{\an3}and that Piri
does not have it.

04:40.813 --> 04:41.748
[shop bell ringing]

04:41.814 --> 04:42.882
- What do you need?

04:42.949 --> 04:44.817
- Yes, hello.
I'm a dad now.

04:44.884 --> 04:46.719
{\an1}- Well, what do you want?
A pat on the back?

04:46.786 --> 04:50.089
{\an3}- Oh, no--actually,
I just need some supplies!

04:50.156 --> 04:51.824
{\an1}- All right.
Follow me.

04:51.891 --> 04:52.992
- All right, you're gonna--

04:53.059 --> 04:54.260
{\an1}you're gonna need
some baby food.

04:54.327 --> 04:56.162
{\an1}Ear plugs.
Little booties.

04:56.229 --> 04:57.697
{\an1}- Oh, you're gonna need
some of this,

04:57.764 --> 04:58.765
and maybe one of these.

04:58.831 --> 05:00.299
This is only the beginning.

05:00.366 --> 05:02.201
{\an1}You've got
another mouth to feed.

05:02.268 --> 05:04.003
Another life to ruin.

05:04.070 --> 05:05.171
Hey, do you want new or used?

05:05.238 --> 05:06.172
- Huh?

05:06.239 --> 05:08.041
- You want new or used diapers?

05:08.107 --> 05:09.175
- Whatever's on the top shelf.

05:09.242 --> 05:11.310
- Ah, come on!

05:11.377 --> 05:13.079
- Aah! Aah! Aah!
This is too much!

05:13.146 --> 05:15.314
I have no idea what I'm doing!

05:15.381 --> 05:17.984
- I am very beautiful.

05:18.051 --> 05:18.985
<i>[energetic music]</i>

05:19.052 --> 05:20.319
{\an3}Wait, what?

05:20.386 --> 05:23.189
- Heh-heh.
I still got it.

05:23.256 --> 05:24.824
<i>[happy music]</i>

05:24.891 --> 05:26.259
- Hello, my friends!

05:26.325 --> 05:28.127
{\an3}- Hey!
You're in a good mood.

05:28.194 --> 05:29.395
- Well, Jeremy's going to raise

05:29.462 --> 05:30.663
my baby sister now,

05:30.730 --> 05:32.198
and I'll get to keep the carrot

05:32.265 --> 05:33.733
that is my parent's love.

05:33.800 --> 05:36.402
{\an1}So yeah,
I'm feelin' pretty good.

05:36.469 --> 05:38.971
{\an3}- Jeremy?
Sister? Carrot?

05:39.038 --> 05:40.206
- Oh, well Dade told me

05:40.273 --> 05:42.408
that having siblings
would ruin my life,

05:42.475 --> 05:44.343
{\an1}so I went
and gave the baby to Jeremy!

05:44.410 --> 05:45.945
It's a win-win.

05:46.012 --> 05:47.213
- Are you serious?

05:47.280 --> 05:48.514
{\an1}- Yeah!

05:48.581 --> 05:50.450
{\an3}- Have you been
drinking crazy juice?

05:50.516 --> 05:53.953
- No, just regular
100% apple juice.

05:54.020 --> 05:55.421
- You kidnapped your baby sister

05:55.488 --> 05:57.190
and gave her to Jeremy?

05:57.256 --> 05:58.825
What were you thinking?

05:58.891 --> 06:00.560
- Uh--

06:00.626 --> 06:02.762
Oh, my gosh!
What was I thinking?

06:02.829 --> 06:04.831
{\an1}There is literally
nothing more beautiful

06:04.897 --> 06:07.867
{\an1}than the love
shared between siblings.

06:07.934 --> 06:08.868
{\an3}- I concur.

06:08.935 --> 06:09.869
{\an1}- Ow.

06:09.936 --> 06:12.004
both: Heh-heh-heh-heh-heh.

06:12.071 --> 06:13.940
{\an1}- Oh, man.
What have I done?

06:14.006 --> 06:17.443
{\an1}I have to go get
that egg back!

06:17.510 --> 06:20.379
{\an3}- You'd never give me away
to Jeremy, would you?

06:20.446 --> 06:23.483
{\an3}Aah!
Heh, cool.

06:23.549 --> 06:25.451
<i>[silly music]</i>

06:25.518 --> 06:27.653
- Whoa-ho-ho!

06:27.720 --> 06:28.654
{\an3}- Jeremy!

06:28.721 --> 06:29.455
{\an1}- Aah!

06:29.522 --> 06:30.456
I made a mistake.

06:30.523 --> 06:31.424
I need that egg back!

06:31.491 --> 06:33.159
- Egg? Oh, w-what egg?

06:33.226 --> 06:34.827
I don't know about an egg!

06:34.894 --> 06:36.028
- The big round egg

06:36.095 --> 06:37.830
{\an3}I gently tucked
into your backside?

06:37.897 --> 06:38.998
- That was you?

06:39.065 --> 06:40.166
Oh, well, I guess that does make

06:40.233 --> 06:41.968
{\an1}a lot more sense--
I mean, egg?

06:42.034 --> 06:43.102
Oh, I don't--

06:43.169 --> 06:44.303
{\an1}oh--oh--
wow, look!

06:44.370 --> 06:45.705
What's that behind you?

06:45.772 --> 06:48.007
{\an3}- Trees.
They're just trees, Jeremy.

06:48.074 --> 06:49.809
Please stay focused.

06:49.876 --> 06:50.910
{\an1}- Aww.

06:50.977 --> 06:51.911
{\an1}[panting]

06:51.978 --> 06:53.146
{\an3}- Hey!

06:53.212 --> 06:54.647
- I'm sorry, Harvey!

06:54.714 --> 06:55.648
[sobbing]

06:55.715 --> 06:56.849
[grunts]

06:56.916 --> 06:58.351
- Hey, are you okay?

06:58.417 --> 07:00.553
- Oh, yeah.
I'm fine, thanks.

07:00.620 --> 07:01.587
- You're welcome.

07:01.654 --> 07:03.122
{\an1}Now tell me
where the egg is!

07:03.189 --> 07:04.657
- Aah!

07:04.724 --> 07:07.426
- I couldn't handle
the pressures of parenthood,

07:07.493 --> 07:09.929
so I left her at Randl's shop!

07:09.996 --> 07:12.431
Oh, gosh, I'm sorry.

07:13.399 --> 07:14.433
- What?

07:14.500 --> 07:16.302
{\an1}- I'm comin',
egg sister!

07:17.370 --> 07:18.538
- Dear diary,

07:18.604 --> 07:21.474
it has been a rough day.

07:21.541 --> 07:23.342
<i>- Egg?</i>
<i>What egg?</i>

07:23.409 --> 07:25.278
{\an3}Oh, the egg
that Jeremy left here!

07:25.344 --> 07:27.079
- Yes!
- Just sold it.

07:27.146 --> 07:29.282
{\an3}The last thing I need
is someone else around here

07:29.348 --> 07:30.750
nagging me all day.

07:30.817 --> 07:32.685
- Randl, did you wash your bits?

07:32.752 --> 07:35.121
{\an1}- Ma!
My bits are fine!

07:35.188 --> 07:36.923
- You have dirty bits.

07:36.989 --> 07:38.391
- You sold her?

07:38.457 --> 07:40.459
Well, who'd you sell her to?

07:40.526 --> 07:43.663
<i>[adventurous music]</i>

07:43.729 --> 07:51.671
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:58.845 --> 07:59.912
- There she is!

07:59.979 --> 08:00.913
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:02.315 --> 08:04.150
Thanks, cool and pretty bug.

08:04.217 --> 08:05.651
[bugs buzzing]

08:05.718 --> 08:07.053
I'm comin', sis!

08:07.119 --> 08:08.287
- Huh?

08:08.354 --> 08:11.524
Wow, a beautiful egg
of my very own.

08:11.591 --> 08:13.392
I know just what to do with it!

08:13.459 --> 08:14.660
Ha!

08:14.727 --> 08:15.828
- What?

08:15.895 --> 08:16.662
No!

08:16.729 --> 08:18.731
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

08:18.798 --> 08:19.732
Oh, no.

08:19.799 --> 08:22.602
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:22.668 --> 08:25.304
Okay, I know
she's somewhere in these rocks.

08:25.371 --> 08:26.706
I'll just check each and every

08:26.772 --> 08:29.909
one of them systematically.

08:29.976 --> 08:30.943
Nope.

08:32.812 --> 08:33.746
Nope.

08:35.114 --> 08:42.054
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:43.322 --> 08:45.157
Nope.

08:45.224 --> 08:49.262
Just a rock.
Not a baby.

08:49.328 --> 08:50.696
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:50.763 --> 08:51.797
[sighs]

08:51.864 --> 08:52.598
Little sis?

08:52.665 --> 08:54.400
I hope you can hear me.

08:54.467 --> 08:56.903
I--I know I let you down,

08:56.969 --> 08:58.237
and I'm sorry,

08:58.304 --> 09:01.107
but I promise
I'm not gonna stop looking

09:01.173 --> 09:02.408
until I find you.

09:02.475 --> 09:05.244
I'm not gonna leave you again.

09:05.311 --> 09:09.448
♪ Little sister of mine ♪

09:09.515 --> 09:13.519
♪ I hope you hatch really soon ♪

09:13.586 --> 09:16.389
♪ 'Cause once you're here ♪

09:16.455 --> 09:18.891
♪ We'll have so much fun ♪

09:18.958 --> 09:23.863
♪ Playing all day in the sun ♪

09:23.930 --> 09:24.864
<i>[egg rustling]</i>

09:24.931 --> 09:28.334
Huh? What was--

09:28.401 --> 09:32.471
♪ Little sister of mine ♪

09:32.538 --> 09:36.008
♪ I'm your big brother, Harvey ♪

09:36.075 --> 09:40.479
♪ And I'll always
be there for you ♪

09:40.546 --> 09:42.281
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:42.348 --> 09:45.985
♪ 'Cause that's what
big brothers do ♪

09:46.052 --> 09:49.822
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:49.889 --> 09:51.824
- Oh,
there you are, sweetie!

09:51.891 --> 09:53.526
{\an1}Did you and your sister
have fun today?

09:53.592 --> 09:55.027
- He's so nurturing.

09:55.094 --> 09:57.730
- Um, yeah, kind of.

09:57.797 --> 10:01.467
Well, actually I, uh--

10:01.534 --> 10:03.569
{\an3}[gasps]

10:03.636 --> 10:04.704
both: [gasping]

10:04.770 --> 10:06.639
- Whoa, my gosh!
It's happening!

10:06.706 --> 10:07.873
Okay, okay.
Everyone stay calm!

10:07.940 --> 10:09.208
I'll just gather what we need.

10:09.275 --> 10:10.242
Got to have a lamp.

10:10.309 --> 10:12.078
Okay. Okay.
Tire pump.

10:12.144 --> 10:13.579
Keep breathing, Miriam!

10:13.646 --> 10:14.914
{\an1}- Irving,
we packed the duffel bag

10:14.981 --> 10:17.516
{\an1}for the hospital weeks ago,
remember?

10:17.583 --> 10:20.720
- Oh.
Right.

10:20.786 --> 10:22.722
<i>[jazzy music]</i>

10:22.788 --> 10:25.458
{\an3}- Oh, gosh.
I'm so nervous.

10:25.524 --> 10:26.993
What if she doesn't like me?

10:27.059 --> 10:29.295
{\an1}- Dude, of course
she's gonna like you.

10:29.362 --> 10:31.464
- Yeah!
You're so likeable.

10:31.530 --> 10:34.600
- Okay!
Who wants to see a baby?

10:34.667 --> 10:36.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:36.202 --> 10:37.536
- Here she is!

10:37.603 --> 10:38.671
Come and say hello

10:38.738 --> 10:41.107
to Harvey's new sister,

10:41.173 --> 10:42.341
{\an3}Michelle.

10:42.408 --> 10:44.810
{\an1}- Aww!
She's so cute.

10:44.877 --> 10:47.980
{\an3}- And so fresh
and untouched by the world!

10:48.047 --> 10:49.915
{\an3}[hacking]

10:51.083 --> 10:52.852
{\an1}- Okay, I think
that's enough time

10:52.918 --> 10:54.453
with the baby for you two.

10:54.520 --> 10:55.621
- Hi, Michelle.

10:55.688 --> 10:57.490
I'm your big brother, Harvey.

10:57.556 --> 10:59.125
Nice to meet you, bugaboo.

10:59.191 --> 11:01.594
{\an3}- [yawns]

11:01.660 --> 11:04.663
- Oh, gosh,
she's like an angel.

11:04.730 --> 11:06.399
{\an1}- Heh.
She sure is, bud.

11:06.465 --> 11:11.103
{\an1}Our perfect,
sweet baby angel.

11:11.170 --> 11:14.106
<i>[evil music]</i>

11:16.642 --> 11:19.578
<i>[happy music]</i>

11:19.645 --> 11:21.547
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:21.614 --> 11:24.683
- [yawning]

11:24.750 --> 11:26.619
- She's finally asleep.

11:26.685 --> 11:28.387
{\an3}- Shh.

11:28.454 --> 11:29.555
[thud]

11:29.622 --> 11:31.357
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:31.424 --> 11:33.092
- Whoa!

11:33.159 --> 11:35.928
These pancakes are neat,
Grandpa Aiden.

11:35.995 --> 11:37.797
- Aw, thanks, Harvey.

11:37.863 --> 11:40.633
Try not to flip out about it.

11:40.699 --> 11:44.737
[both laughing]

11:44.804 --> 11:46.639
- Oh Aiden,
that was terrible.

11:46.705 --> 11:48.908
I mean, really,
really, really bad.

11:48.974 --> 11:51.510
{\an3}- Grandma Miley!
Here's your pancake.

11:51.577 --> 11:52.978
- Thank you, gumdrop.

11:53.045 --> 11:55.781
{\an3}- And here's your pancake,
Grandpa Roland.

11:55.848 --> 11:57.716
<i>[thunder rumbling]</i>

11:57.783 --> 11:59.251
- Mm.

11:59.318 --> 12:02.288
- So Harvey, do you remember
your first pancake?

12:02.354 --> 12:05.458
- My first pancake.

12:05.524 --> 12:09.128
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:09.195 --> 12:10.129
[gasps]

12:10.196 --> 12:13.466
Whee!

12:13.532 --> 12:15.134
That's exactly how it happened.

12:15.201 --> 12:17.436
Michelle's gonna love
her first pancake.

12:17.503 --> 12:19.872
This is going to be
the best morning ever!

12:19.939 --> 12:22.308
[thunder roars]

12:22.374 --> 12:23.709
Well, that was weird.

12:26.745 --> 12:33.686
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:33.752 --> 12:36.355
One final touch--there!

12:36.422 --> 12:37.756
To keep the germs off.

12:37.823 --> 12:40.726
- Oh my, what a considerate
big brother you are.

12:40.793 --> 12:42.128
- Thank you!
[clears throat]

12:42.194 --> 12:45.197
Michelle, your pancake's ready!

12:45.264 --> 12:46.465
Pancake!

12:46.532 --> 12:47.967
- Harvey, you got
to let the baby sleep.

12:48.033 --> 12:49.068
Your mother and I haven't had

12:49.135 --> 12:50.936
any peace and quiet for weeks.

12:51.003 --> 12:53.405
{\an1}- I'm gonna--
I'm gonna win the race.

12:53.472 --> 12:54.740
{\an1}[snores]

12:54.807 --> 12:56.208
- Well, what if we just

12:56.275 --> 12:57.910
wake her up for five minutes?

12:57.977 --> 13:00.379
I mean, this is pretty important
if you think about it.

13:00.446 --> 13:01.780
- You know what, bud?

13:01.847 --> 13:04.250
{\an3}Let's just put that
on a back burner, okay?

13:04.316 --> 13:05.217
[yawns]

13:05.284 --> 13:06.519
Now, if you'll excuse me,

13:06.585 --> 13:07.653
I got to go catch

13:07.720 --> 13:10.589
this last train to Sleep Town.

13:10.656 --> 13:13.526
Toot, toot.

13:13.592 --> 13:14.527
[snoring]

13:14.593 --> 13:15.594
Dad?

13:15.661 --> 13:17.229
[Michelle screaming and crying]

13:17.296 --> 13:19.064
{\an1}- Don't worry!
We're coming! We're coming!

13:19.131 --> 13:21.400
- Now hold on.
I don't want to miss a thing.

13:21.467 --> 13:22.801
[all murmuring]

13:22.868 --> 13:24.170
- What does she need?

13:24.236 --> 13:25.704
Diaper?
Is she hungry?

13:25.771 --> 13:27.673
- I just want to sleep!

13:27.740 --> 13:29.675
{\an1}[sobbing]

13:29.742 --> 13:30.676
{\an3}- Mm.

13:30.743 --> 13:32.311
- I'll get the baby.

13:32.378 --> 13:34.046
{\an3}- Please, dear.
Let me take care of it.

13:34.113 --> 13:35.781
You--you go lie down.

13:35.848 --> 13:38.083
- Don't tell me what to do, Mom.

13:38.150 --> 13:39.919
<i>- Here we are</i>
<i>with big brother Harvey.</i>

13:39.985 --> 13:41.720
{\an3}<i>- Huh?</i>
<i>Oh, hi, Grandpa Aiden.</i>

13:41.787 --> 13:45.591
{\an3}<i>I'm gonna go grab some</i>
<i>silverware for Michelle.</i>

13:45.658 --> 13:47.726
<i>- Ah, and here's</i>
<i>the pancake itself.</i>

13:47.793 --> 13:49.528
<i>All ready to go.</i>

13:49.595 --> 13:51.363
<i>Oh, and here's</i>
<i>sweet little Michelle!</i>

13:51.430 --> 13:53.732
<i>Say hi, Michelle!</i>

13:53.799 --> 13:55.968
<i>- Shh. Shh.</i>

13:56.035 --> 13:58.671
- Oh, baby, oh, baby,
oh, baby sister.

13:58.737 --> 14:00.773
Get ready to--huh?

14:00.839 --> 14:03.776
The TV remote?
That's silly.

14:03.842 --> 14:05.844
{\an1}Guys?
Where's the silverware?

14:05.911 --> 14:08.247
{\an1}It's not in the--oh!
Never mind.

14:09.582 --> 14:10.516
{\an3}- [crying]

14:10.583 --> 14:11.550
[thunder roars]

14:11.617 --> 14:13.852
- Oh, no. The lights.

14:15.654 --> 14:17.723
- Aah!

14:17.790 --> 14:18.991
- I found the silverware.

14:19.058 --> 14:21.193
And now, without further ado,

14:21.260 --> 14:24.964
I'd like to present
Michelle's very first pancake.

14:25.030 --> 14:27.366
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

14:27.433 --> 14:28.234
Huh?

14:28.300 --> 14:29.902
Wait, where'd it go?

14:29.969 --> 14:31.904
I--I don't understand.

14:31.971 --> 14:35.975
I--I lost Michelle's
first pancake!

14:39.545 --> 14:41.347
- Harvey, sweetie,
I think you're taking

14:41.413 --> 14:43.882
this pancake thing
a little too seriously.

14:43.949 --> 14:46.885
{\an1}- But Grandma,
look how sad she is!

14:46.952 --> 14:49.922
- [crazy baby noises]

14:49.989 --> 14:51.390
Wait a minute.

14:51.457 --> 14:53.259
Pancakes don't go missin'
on their own.

14:53.325 --> 14:54.260
[gasps]

14:54.326 --> 14:55.494
There's a little thief among us!

14:55.561 --> 14:57.229
I've got
to bring them to justice!

14:57.296 --> 14:58.964
Grandpa Aiden,
you were a cop.

14:59.031 --> 15:00.633
- Yup, I was a desk cop.

15:00.699 --> 15:01.867
- That's the best kind.

15:01.934 --> 15:03.235
What do we do first?

15:03.302 --> 15:05.070
Well, first,
we are going to need

15:05.137 --> 15:06.472
to open a case file.

15:06.538 --> 15:08.774
- Cool!

15:08.841 --> 15:11.010
{\an8}<i>[fun music]</i>

15:11.076 --> 15:12.544
- That's adorable.

15:12.611 --> 15:14.613
- You remember
the next step, detective?

15:14.680 --> 15:15.981
{\an3}- Oh, yeah.

15:16.048 --> 15:18.050
{\an3}"One:
search for clues."

15:18.117 --> 15:19.685
Now, to go all the way back

15:19.752 --> 15:21.387
to the scene of the crime!

15:21.453 --> 15:25.457
{\an3}And we're here.
Time to get clues.

15:25.524 --> 15:26.859
Hmm.

15:26.925 --> 15:30.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:30.195 --> 15:32.765
Nothing on the banisters.

15:32.831 --> 15:35.067
Nothing in my sock drawer.

15:35.134 --> 15:37.770
{\an3}[coughs]
Not under the bed.

15:37.836 --> 15:39.905
Still not on the banisters.

15:39.972 --> 15:41.307
Curious.

15:41.373 --> 15:43.208
- Oh, you're a fast detective.

15:43.275 --> 15:45.711
A break-fast detective.
[laughs]

15:45.778 --> 15:47.212
- That was awful.

15:47.279 --> 15:49.281
Any luck finding the culprit?

15:49.348 --> 15:50.416
- Not yet.

15:50.482 --> 15:54.053
So far, we've found nothing.

15:54.119 --> 15:56.755
"Step two: interview suspects."

15:56.822 --> 15:57.956
Okay.

15:58.023 --> 15:59.358
[gasps]

15:59.425 --> 16:02.194
You--

16:02.261 --> 16:05.397
<i>[mysterious music]</i>

16:05.464 --> 16:08.167
{\an3}Where were you when
the pancake went missing?

16:08.233 --> 16:09.868
- Uh--uh--I--
I was at the office.

16:09.935 --> 16:10.936
I mean, the kitchen.

16:11.003 --> 16:12.237
Uh, sweeping
up the chimney.

16:12.304 --> 16:13.972
I was stuck in a chimney.

16:14.039 --> 16:15.741
Uh--no, I was cutting my beard.

16:15.808 --> 16:17.710
Oh, wait.
Wait. The camera.

16:17.776 --> 16:18.944
{\an1}I have an alibi.
Phew.

16:19.011 --> 16:21.413
[camera beeps]

16:21.480 --> 16:22.748
{\an1}Hmm.

16:22.815 --> 16:24.616
- Aiden, can you grab
a bottle for Michelle?

16:24.683 --> 16:25.984
Aiden!

16:26.051 --> 16:28.821
Have you been filming
my butt this whole time?

16:28.887 --> 16:29.822
- [laughing]

16:29.888 --> 16:30.823
You got me!

16:30.889 --> 16:31.824
- [laughing]

16:31.890 --> 16:34.326
Oh, no.
The lights.

16:34.393 --> 16:36.028
- Well, I learned something

16:36.095 --> 16:37.463
about you today.

16:37.529 --> 16:38.397
Grandpa Aiden,

16:38.464 --> 16:40.299
you are innocent of all charges.

16:40.366 --> 16:42.735
- Phew. Great. Who's next?

16:42.801 --> 16:44.937
<i>- And Lonksi takes the ball</i>
<i>up the field.</i>

16:45.003 --> 16:46.438
<i>He's going.</i>
<i>He's going.</i>

16:46.505 --> 16:49.875
- Grandpa Roland--
if that is your real name.

16:49.942 --> 16:52.211
Did you take Michelle's pancake?

16:52.277 --> 16:53.412
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

16:53.479 --> 16:54.413
{\an3}- No.

16:54.480 --> 16:55.414
{\an1}- Okay!

16:55.481 --> 16:56.648
Grandpa Roland:

16:56.715 --> 16:58.684
cleared of all charges.

16:58.751 --> 17:00.486
Mmm.
- Mm.

17:00.552 --> 17:02.287
{\an1}- Let's move on
to our next suspect.

17:02.354 --> 17:03.088
{\an1}Bye!

17:03.155 --> 17:05.557
Grandma Miley.

17:05.624 --> 17:07.760
- Hello, my baby angel.

17:07.826 --> 17:09.828
- Now, you used to be a judge,

17:09.895 --> 17:11.296
so I'm sure you understand

17:11.363 --> 17:13.898
the importance
of truth and justice

17:13.965 --> 17:15.067
in this situation.

17:15.134 --> 17:16.268
- Indeed I do.

17:16.335 --> 17:17.502
And I know the importance

17:17.569 --> 17:20.138
{\an1}of grandsons having
their cheeks pinched.

17:20.204 --> 17:22.074
- Uh, excuse me Grandma,

17:22.141 --> 17:24.476
{\an3}but I'm working on
an investigation here.

17:24.542 --> 17:26.811
{\an1}- Oh, I'm sorry, detective.
Please carry on.

17:26.878 --> 17:27.980
- Thank you.

17:28.046 --> 17:31.016
{\an3}Now tell me,
do you like pancakes?

17:31.083 --> 17:32.117
- Well, I suppose.

17:32.184 --> 17:33.819
Do you like pancakes?

17:33.886 --> 17:36.054
- Uh, yes, actually, I do.

17:36.121 --> 17:37.389
- That's interesting.

17:37.456 --> 17:39.558
{\an1}So where were you when
the pancake went missing?

17:39.625 --> 17:41.927
{\an3}- Uh, well,
I was in the kitchen.

17:41.994 --> 17:43.529
{\an1}- In the kitchen
eating the pancake?

17:43.595 --> 17:45.464
- No, I was getting silverware.

17:45.531 --> 17:47.466
{\an1}- Silverware
for eating pancakes?

17:47.533 --> 17:49.301
{\an1}Oh, you did just say
how you like pancakes.

17:49.368 --> 17:51.804
{\an3}- What?
I do love pancakes,

17:51.870 --> 17:54.706
{\an3}but not more than
I love my baby sister!

17:54.773 --> 17:56.275
- You know, Harvey, sometimes,

17:56.341 --> 17:59.111
{\an1}when someone commits
a terrible crime,

17:59.178 --> 18:01.380
{\an1}their mind blocks out the memory
to protect them.

18:01.447 --> 18:04.850
{\an3}- [moaning] Maybe I did do it
and I don't remember.

18:04.917 --> 18:07.252
{\an3}Am I capable
of such an atrocity?

18:07.319 --> 18:09.922
Stealing from my very own
flesh and blood?

18:09.988 --> 18:11.123
Who am I?

18:11.190 --> 18:13.926
- I sentence you

18:13.992 --> 18:15.427
to come and sit on my lap.

18:15.494 --> 18:16.562
- Okay.

18:16.628 --> 18:17.763
Oof!

18:19.364 --> 18:21.266
- Honey, I'm just teasing.

18:21.333 --> 18:22.768
You didn't take the pancake.

18:22.835 --> 18:23.769
{\an3}- I didn't?

18:23.836 --> 18:25.070
- No, I'll vouch for you.

18:25.137 --> 18:26.205
- Cool! Okay.

18:26.271 --> 18:28.974
I'll vouch for you too, Grandma.

18:29.041 --> 18:30.309
{\an8}<i>[serious music]</i>

18:30.375 --> 18:32.211
But now the trail's run cold.

18:32.277 --> 18:35.013
{\an1}- Have you tried
retracing your steps?

18:35.080 --> 18:37.115
<i>[playful music]</i>

18:37.182 --> 18:40.986
- [grunting and groaning]

18:41.053 --> 18:42.921
Okay, that's too hard.

18:42.988 --> 18:45.290
Now, I came into the kitchen

18:45.357 --> 18:47.192
to get silverware for Michelle.

18:47.259 --> 18:49.027
But when I checked the drawer,

18:49.094 --> 18:51.263
the only thing
that was in there was

18:51.330 --> 18:53.198
the TV remote!

18:53.265 --> 18:54.333
Well, that's weird.

18:54.399 --> 18:56.401
Why would someone
put this in here?

18:56.468 --> 18:59.037
Everyone knows remotes
don't belong in the kitchen.

18:59.104 --> 19:02.140
They belong on the south edge
of the coffee table.

19:02.207 --> 19:03.141
Huh?

19:03.208 --> 19:04.576
[Grandpa Aiden snoring]

19:04.643 --> 19:06.545
Grandpa Aiden?

19:06.612 --> 19:08.747
Hmm.

19:08.814 --> 19:11.583
- [humming to self]

19:11.650 --> 19:12.618
- Grandpa Aiden!

19:12.684 --> 19:13.452
{\an3}- Whoa!

19:13.519 --> 19:14.686
- Does this belong to you?

19:14.753 --> 19:16.255
- Why, that looks
just like the pen

19:16.321 --> 19:18.357
I bought from
the Fogbark joke shop.

19:18.423 --> 19:20.392
Best $65 I've ever spent.

19:20.459 --> 19:21.894
Well, that can't be the one,

19:21.960 --> 19:25.097
'cause I always keep mine
right here under--what?

19:25.163 --> 19:26.765
Cherry lipstick?

19:26.832 --> 19:27.766
This is the same color

19:27.833 --> 19:29.301
your Grandma Miley wears.

19:29.368 --> 19:31.470
<i>[thunder roaring]</i>

19:31.537 --> 19:33.772
{\an3}- Grandma Miley!
Show us your lipstick.

19:33.839 --> 19:35.240
- Strange, but okay.

19:35.307 --> 19:36.575
Let me just check my purse.

19:36.642 --> 19:37.976
Oh--oh, my.

19:38.043 --> 19:40.178
{\an1}There's a pillow in here,
and it's all drooly!

19:40.245 --> 19:42.581
- A drool-covered pillow?

19:42.648 --> 19:46.184
It all makes perfect sense now!

19:46.251 --> 19:47.786
- What's goin' on in here?

19:47.853 --> 19:48.887
- Come on, Grandpa Roland.

19:48.954 --> 19:51.023
We're about to solve this case!

19:51.089 --> 19:57.930
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:57.996 --> 19:58.931
There!

19:58.997 --> 20:01.934
- [snoring]

20:02.000 --> 20:04.369
[sleep-talking]

20:04.436 --> 20:05.370
[all gasping]

20:05.437 --> 20:06.905
- The pancake!

20:06.972 --> 20:07.940
- Oh, sugar berry,

20:08.006 --> 20:09.775
how did you figure this out?

20:09.841 --> 20:12.544
- Well, allow me to explain.

20:12.611 --> 20:14.346
<i>Ever since Michelle was born,</i>

20:14.413 --> 20:16.548
<i>my dad hasn't</i>
<i>been getting much sleep,</i>

20:16.615 --> 20:18.383
<i>and when he gets real tired,</i>

20:18.450 --> 20:20.652
<i>he starts doing strange things,</i>

20:20.719 --> 20:24.222
<i>like misplacing</i>
<i>the television remote.</i>

20:24.289 --> 20:25.757
- This kitchen is too loud.

20:25.824 --> 20:27.859
Got to turn you down.

20:27.926 --> 20:30.462
[sleep-talking]

20:30.529 --> 20:33.865
<i>- Or taking</i>
<i>Grandpa Aiden's flower pen.</i>

20:33.932 --> 20:34.900
- Okay, boys.

20:34.967 --> 20:36.134
You go watch the baby,

20:36.201 --> 20:37.536
while I go take a nap.

20:37.603 --> 20:38.537
{\an1}[snoring]

20:39.471 --> 20:40.772
<i>- But before that,</i>

20:40.839 --> 20:43.809
<i>he got</i>
<i>into Grandma Miley's purse.</i>

20:43.875 --> 20:46.178
- Ooh, cherry popsicle.

20:46.244 --> 20:49.815
Aah! This tastes terrible.

20:49.881 --> 20:51.350
[Michelle crying]

20:51.416 --> 20:52.784
{\an8}<i>- The whole crime spree began</i>

20:52.851 --> 20:54.953
{\an8}<i>when Dad confused</i>
<i>an innocent pancake</i>

20:55.020 --> 20:56.655
{\an8}<i>as a pillow.</i>

20:56.722 --> 20:59.091
- Oh, no.
The lights!

20:59.157 --> 21:00.759
- [moans]

21:00.826 --> 21:03.061
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:03.128 --> 21:05.864
[moans]

21:05.931 --> 21:06.865
[snoring]

21:06.932 --> 21:08.266
- Dad wasn't trying to ruin

21:08.333 --> 21:10.302
Michelle's pancake experience.

21:10.369 --> 21:12.337
He was just one sleepy dude.

21:12.404 --> 21:15.907
{\an1}I won! Aah.
[snoring]

21:15.974 --> 21:19.177
- Well, then,
I guess this case is closed!

21:19.244 --> 21:20.212
<i>[serious music]</i>

21:20.278 --> 21:21.913
- It was Dad.

21:21.980 --> 21:24.316
<i>[happy music]</i>

21:24.383 --> 21:26.118
- [happy baby noises]

21:26.184 --> 21:29.254
- Harvey, we just want to let
you know how proud we are.

21:29.321 --> 21:30.756
You solved the whole mystery

21:30.822 --> 21:32.024
all by yourself.

21:32.090 --> 21:33.091
{\an1}- Mm.

21:33.158 --> 21:34.660
- Well, I couldn't have done it

21:34.726 --> 21:37.429
without the help
of my awesome grandparents.

21:37.496 --> 21:38.730
- Hey, everyone!

21:38.797 --> 21:41.066
Michelle's about
to take her first bite.

21:41.133 --> 21:43.735
- Ah, here we go!
Oh, boy.

21:43.802 --> 21:45.370
- [squealing]

21:45.437 --> 21:48.573
[frantic gibberish]

21:50.142 --> 21:52.678
[growling and snarling]

21:52.744 --> 21:55.414
[snoring]

21:56.948 --> 21:57.883
{\an1}- Wow.

21:57.949 --> 21:59.885
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:01.687 --> 22:04.823
<i>[cheerful music]</i>

22:04.890 --> 22:12.831
<i>♪ ♪</i>
